modName: Skip Past High Hrothgar A Clean Save
summary: This is a clean un-modded save file for those who wants a good reset. Might also be useful for those that want to have a quick start over.
descriptionHtml:
[center][size=8][color=yellow][font=Comic Sans]      The Character
[img]http://img811.imageshack.us/img811/4145/elant.jpg[/img]
[/font][/color][/size]
[font=\"Franklin Gothic Medium\"]+ Male lvl 1, High Elf.
+ Not leveled with a few saved up perk points (None used)
+ Stamina, Health, and Magicka is also untouched
+ Some skill levels was raised a bit from dungeoning (Destruction and Archery mostly)
+ Finished up small riverwood quests and chatter
+ Finished Bleak Falls Barrows quest
+ Completed some minor errands quest in whiterun
+ Killed First Dragon on West Tower
+ Summoned and met the Greybeards from High Hrothgar[/font]

[size=\"3\"][i]For anything else just check the quest menu for things I\'ve done and quest activated. Should be just minimal and minor things.[/i][/size]

[color=\"#483D8B\"][font=\"Century Gothic\"]For those that don\'t know how to change or re-customize your character:[/font][/color]
[b][color=red]Use console command \" ~ \" key and type showracemenu[/color][/b]

Your character will start at Dragons Reach. 
[color=orange]
Why I did this? I got tired of redoing these quests at the beginning. >.<; If you\'re like me and you always screw up your game with mods and updates.. then this might be able to help you out. I left the main storyline past High Hrothgar coz I feel like that\'s where the Dragonborn can branch off to doing any quests and go anywhere to follow whatever path you want to take. [/color]

[color=skyblue]~If this file was helpful to you, feel free to endorse it~[/color]

[/center]
author: Scepth
